what is a loving dog breed that needs little exercise for my dad that has depression i think buying a dog for my dad would help him through depression my dad is years old and he does not get out of the house much he is very unfit and i want a dog that will be a loyal companion clean and with a bit of luck lift his spirits hopefully there is a dog breed out there that fits the bill please help me help my dad by suggesting a suitable dog breed i would definitely suggest asking your dad first before purchasing rescuing as he might not want one or even just snoop around and ask innocent questions about dogs if you want it to be a surprise just so you don't waste your time or money anyway yorkshire terriers are small dogs they don't shed a lot and they're perfect for apartments as they can get all their exercise inside which would be perfect for your dad as he doesn't get out much and they're extremely lovable i forgot to mention you could buy him a slightly older dog from a rescue as they're usually settled down and enjoy things more slowly and they've been spayed already i wouldn't suggest a new puppy Cat Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Pet skunk Domestic rabbit Shaggy dog story West Highland White Terrier The Fairly OddParents Kerry Blue Terrier Mixed-breed dog American Pit Bull Terrier Social rule Whippet Game show Yorkshire Terrier Francis Bacon (painter) Dog breeding Housebreaking Hamster Border Terrier Companion dog Great Dane Pit bull Pug Alaskan husky American Eskimo Dog Border Collie Friends Fancy rat Welsh Terrier Labrador Retriever Shetland Sheepdog Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Ferret Equine conformation Japanese Chin Airedale Terrier Miniature Fox Terrier Golden Retriever Havanese Working dog Soft-Coated Wheaten Terrier Dog breed Oh My Goddess! Maltese (dog) Jack Russell Terrier Kim Possible American Kennel Club Basset Hound Terrier Breed standard Skye Terrier Piccolo Junior Saga Hey Jude Ron Weasley Bernese Mountain Dog The Death Gate Cycle Trailer 